How to run Networked Graphs

Configuration

There are two ways for configuring this. First to look at the readme file in the DistributedSail directory and follow its instructions. According to Simon Schenk that's all that I should need.
These instructions are:
Download the project (bzr branch lp:networkedgraphs)
Build the project: mvn install, mvn eclipse:eclipse
Use it (next section)
Usage

Check out
http://www.openrdf.org/doc/sesame2/users/
for Sesame information
I guess I have to configure a repository,
where should I store it? In memory, it is possible to configure it as a normal Sesame repository accessed by means of the API
how do I configure it? just API commands
how is it accessed? later on, you configure the elements in the repository by an n3 file
Is it executed by the DistributedSail or by the standard Sail from Sesame? distirbuted sail
Configuration file example:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>.
@prefix rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>.
@prefix rep: <http://www.openrdf.org/config/repository#>.
@prefix sr: <http://www.openrdf.org/config/repository/sail#>.
@prefix sail: <http://www.openrdf.org/config/sail#>.
@prefix ns: <http://www.openrdf.org/config/sail/native#>.
@prefix ds: <http://isweb.uni-koblenz.de/Ontologies/DistributedSAIL/config/sail#>.
[] a rep:Repository ;
   rep:repositoryID "{%Repository ID|federator%}" ;
   rdfs:label "{%Repository title|Distributed Sail with RepositorySourceFinder%}" ;
   rep:repositoryImpl [
      rep:repositoryType "openrdf:SailRepository" ;
      sr:sailImpl [
         sail:sailType "isweb:NGSail" ;
         sail:delegate [      sr:sailImpl [
            sail:sailType "isweb:DistributedSail" ;
            ds:hasSourceFinder [
               ds:hasConfGraph {%Configuration Graph|<http://demetrios.isweb.uni-koblenz.de/federator/endpoints>%};
               a ds:RepositorySourceFinder
            ];
            sail:delegate [
               sail:sailType "openrdf:NativeStore" ;
               ns:tripleIndexes "{%Triple indexes|spoc,posc%}"
            ];
         ];
      ]
   ].
Once the repository has been configured we have to tell to DistributedSail to which sails (aka networked graphs) we can access. This is done by means of another configuration file in which there are specified all the NGs available.
